                  <bindingDesc resp="#BCBB">
                     <binding notAfter="1525" notBefore="1475">
                        <p>15th century, late, or early 16th century, <placeName key="place_1000080">Italian</placeName> (manuscript from the nunnery of the 
                           <orgName>Poor Clares of Assisi</orgName>): wood boards; dark brown leather, blind-tooled with lines, stamps and strapwork; 
                           original spine lost; remains of a single central clasp with part of a brown-leather strap (not original?) and a brass catch-plate 
                           with a boss-like protrusion on the back cover; edges discoloured, probably plain. Rebacked by the Bodleian, later 19th century (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>. 1877–1887?), 
                           when it was classified amongst manuscripts with a 'Liturg.' shelfmark</p>
                        
                  <!-- Add authority record -->                  

                     </binding>
